#Text=Do Festival Makeup
#Text=When you are doing your makeup for a festival , you may be concerned about achieving the right look and making sure that your makeup does not run off of your face .
#Text=This festival makeup look is bright , colorful , and long-lasting .
#Text=Whether you are new to applying makeup or an experienced make-up wearer , you can create this beautiful look in minutes and feel confident that you will look great all day .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Applying Eye Makeup
#Text=Prep your face .
#Text=Before you apply your eye makeup , you will need to create a base .
#Text=This will help to ensure that your eye makeup lasts all day long .
#Text=Start with a clean , moisturized face .
#Text=Start by cleansing your face with a gentle cleanser , then apply a light moisturizer to your face and neck to reduce the appearance of fine lines .
#Text=You may also want to apply sunscreen with an SPF 30 or higher rating to protect your skin from sun damage .
#Text=Apply foundation .
#Text=Next , apply your foundation as usual .
#Text=Make sure that you cover your entire face and blend well around the edges of your face .
#Text=You can also apply some concealer to provide coverage for blemishes , discoloration , or dark circles under your eyes .
#Text=Prime your eyelids .
#Text=To prepare your eyelids for your eyeshadow , apply some primer to your eyelids .
#Text=This will help to prevent the eyeshadow from melting into your creases as the day goes on .
#Text=Shape your eyebrows .
#Text=Define your eyebrows as you normally would .
#Text=Apply an orange color to your crease .
#Text=After you have prepped your face , apply a matte orange eyeshadow to your creases .
#Text=This will help to transition between your skin and the other colors that you apply .
#Text=You can apply more than one layer depending on the color of your skin .
#Text=Add bronze eyeshadow to your lids .
#Text=Next , apply your bronze eyeshadow to your eyelids .
#Text=Make sure that you apply lots of bronze to create a noticeable shimmery look .
#Text=You may need to pat the color onto your lids rather than brushing it to get the coverage that you will need .
#Text=Keep layering the eyeshadow until you achieve the color saturation that you want .
#Text=Highlight your inner corners with bronze eyeshadow .
#Text=Use your highlighter brush to apply a small dab of highlighter to the inner part of your eyelids , right next to your tear ducts .
#Text=This will help to brighten your eyes and catch the light .
#Text=You can also add highlighter to your brow bone if desired .
#Text=However , you might want to use a lighter color to highlight these areas , such as a champagne or light gold color .
#Text=Apply some metallic liner to your lower inner lash line .
#Text=To further accentuate the inside of your eyes , apply a small amount of metallic liquid eyeliner to your lower lash line .
#Text=Make sure that the line is even and straight .
#Text=You may need to go over the area a couple of times to get the right coverage .
#Text=After you apply the liner , tap on the lined area to help diffuse the color and blend it in with your skin .
#Text=Line your lower lash line with aqua eyeshadow .
#Text=Next , take a liner brush and use it to apply aqua eyeshadow to your lower lash line .
#Text=You can build the color with extra layers for a bold look , or just apply one layer for a more subtle look .
#Text=Finish your eye look with mascara .
#Text=To complete your eye look , apply two coats of mascara to your upper lashes and then apply one coat to your lower lashes .
#Text=Make sure that you wipe off any excess mascara from the brush before you apply the mascara .
#Text=Otherwise , you may end up with clumps .
#Text=If possible , use a mascara that is labeled as “ waterproof , ”
#Text=“ long lasting , ” or “ all day wear . ”
#Text=These products tend to last longer than regular mascaras .
#Text=Applying Highlighter and Lipstick
#Text=Brush some highlighter onto your cheekbones .
#Text=To ensure a glowing complexion , take a large fluffy brush and sweep some highlighter just above your cheekbones .
#Text=You only need a little highlighter to create a slight shimmer to your skin .
#Text=Do n't apply too much or you may look washed out or metallic .
#Text=Dab some highlighter onto your nose and cupid ’s bow .
#Text=Use your finger or a small fluffy brush to dab a bit of highlighter onto the tip of your nose and to your cupid ’s bow .
#Text=Your cupid ’s bow is the curved area just above the center of your upper lip .
#Text=If you want , you can also apply a small amount of highlighter to the bridge of your nose , right between your eyes .
#Text=Apply a matte nude color to your lips .
#Text=Since this eyeshadow look is so colorful , you do not need to do much to your lips .
#Text=A coat of nude lipstick will provide enough color to finish your look .
#Text=You can line your lips first with the same color ( or a similar one ) and then apply the lipstick .
